@andr3 @drewcoffman any web3 organization that is serious about disrupting anti-NFTers needs to integrate learning & positive use-cases into their communications strategy.

best approach is, ignore the grumps & create content that is accessible & makes the potential benefits of the tech compelling.

@andr3 @drewcoffman Unfortunately I don't think engaging with this crowd on Twitter is the answer; the platform does NOT enable good faith debates. 

Most web2 social platforms are outrage factories, because of the way engagement is incentivized via algorithms.

@drewcoffman yep. i think the key nuance the anti-NFT crowd is missing is that NFTs are like anything else in society. 

There are undeniably scams & bad people in the space, but also brilliant creative people using innovative technology to do very important & cool things.

@drewcoffman @belGIANgwaffles +1. i listened to a podcast ft. @hankgreen, and he was talking about how platforms should change to support creators and I was like... 

sir what you are describing is an NFT.

@drewcoffman whew. we are in a race with a small group of LOUD anti-NFTers to make sure the narrative about web3 that gets to ordinary folks is inspiring & compelling. 

we need to be able to put forward concise, simple arguments that disprove anti-NFTers' poor understanding of this tech...
